            "bestRating": "5",
            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "I've passed out from HCS, Thus, I am going to share an honest review.\nPros: The education is brilliant. All the teachers are educated and have deep knowledge of their subjects. Lab practicals are conducted on regular basis. They try to instil moral habits and values in their students. Infrastructure is great, medical facilities available.\nCons : No focus on extracurricular activities. No outside the world knowledge is given to students. No such involvement in sports activities. Discipline is good but sometimes the cases are extreme, a few teachers do partiality amongst students.\nExtra- access to office facilities is provided, sometimes visits to colleges and adventure parks were planned.\nPersonally in my 14 years in this school the SUPW teacher didn't even care to teach the students how to even draw an eye. Only the students who could afford to take musical classes at home were allowed to TOUCH the musical instruments. No music related knowledge was shared by the teacher in 14 years because for every music class students were asked to sing prayer songs. Music teacher used to pass comments on the looks of students and was sometimes harsh on them.\nNo extra Club, sports, mind shaping activities are done to improve the interpersonal skills of senior students.\nPersonally these skills are as important as education is, if not polished students face a hard time in college.\nI love this school and I don't have any personal war with it, this was an honest review written after a few years of passing from there. I wrote it thinking it might help someone and to give a reality check.",
